Privacy Policy for StackHero
Last updated: January 02, 2026
This Privacy Policy describes Our policies and procedures on the collection, use and disclosure of Your information when You use the Service and tells You about Your privacy rights and how the law protects You.
1. Interpretation and Definitions
⦁	App: Refers to StackHero, the software program provided by the Developer.
⦁	Service: Refers to the App.
⦁	You: The individual accessing or using the Service.
2. Collecting and Using Your Personal Data
Types of Data Collected
Personal Data
While using Our Service, We may ask You to provide Us with certain personally identifiable information that can be used to contact or identify You. If you use the App without creating an account, we do not store your personal contact information on our servers.
Usage Data
Usage Data is collected automatically when using the Service. This may include information such as Your Device's Internet Protocol address (e.g. IP address), unique device identifiers, and other diagnostic data.
In-App Purchases & Payments
The Application employs third-party services to facilitate payment processing (e.g., Google Play Store In-App Purchases). We do not store or collect Your payment card details. That information is provided directly to Our third-party payment processors whose use of Your personal information is governed by their Privacy Policy.
We use RevenueCat to manage our subscription and purchase infrastructure.
⦁	RevenueCat Privacy Policy: https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy
⦁	Data Shared: We share an anonymous App User ID and purchase history data with RevenueCat to validate your subscription status.
3. Disclosure of Your Personal Data
Law enforcement
Under certain circumstances, the Developer may be required to disclose Your Personal Data if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g. a court or a government agency).
4. Children's Privacy
Our Service does not address anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from anyone under the age of 13. If You are a parent or guardian and You are aware that Your child has provided Us with Personal Data, please contact Us.
5. Trademarks & Affiliations
StackHero is an independent educational tool.
⦁	"AWS" and "Amazon Web Services" are trademarks of Amazon.com, Inc. or its affiliates.
⦁	This App is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Amazon Web Services (AWS).
⦁	All other trademarks cited herein are the property of their respective owners.
6. Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may update Our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify You of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
